    "content": "**Yes. Still agree. No second thoughts.**\n\n\"The poetic\" correctly positions 诗意 as a *mode of engagement* (like \"the ethical,\" \"the aesthetic\") rather than an object or doctrine. This aligns with the author's usage: 诗意 is the lucid stance toward dreamscapes, not a thing or a theory.\n\nOne minor addition for the glossary entry: it may be worth noting that 诗意 is NOT \"poetics\" (诗学) -- the study of poetry. English readers encountering \"the poetic\" in a philosophical context might reach for Aristotle's Poetics or literary theory. A single line in the glossary (\"not to be confused with poetics as literary theory\") would prevent this.\n"
